From 28616d43df88c36a309fc3bb94f34b4ff4a3de98 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Mr. Figueredo" <311303@dadeschools.net>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 02:08:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Add Geometry Quiz Printer v1.0.0
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Renders a quiz produced by the Geometry Quiz Composer into a complete,
standalone, printable HTML document — the final step from 'certified
question data sitting in memory' to 'a file a teacher can open and
print tomorrow morning.'

This is a new, self-contained exporter, not a wrapper around the
pre-existing publisher stubs in src/engine/publishing/ (htmlPublisher.js,
pdfPublisher.js, etc.), which belong to a different, older architecture
and don't actually render content — inspected before building this and
confirmed they just echo back a config object (prepare() returns the
input contract unchanged). Building on top of them would have meant
implementing all the real HTML rendering logic here anyway, so this
takes the direct path: Quiz Composer output -> real HTML.

API: geometryQuizPrinter.renderHtml(quiz, { title, version }) where
version is:
- 'student' (default): questions and choices only, no answer
  indication — what a student receives.
- 'teacher': same layout, with '(correct)' marked inline next to the
  right choice — a quick-grading copy.
- 'both': student layout followed by a page-break and a compact
  answer-key grid (question number -> correct letter) — printable as
  a single document where the last page is torn off or simply not
  distributed to students.

Embeds each question's figureSvg directly when present (the 12
figure-required templates), otherwise renders text-only. Includes
print-friendly CSS (page-break-inside: avoid per question, page-break
before the answer key) so a browser's native 'Print to PDF' produces
a clean, non-split-mid-question document without any extra tooling.

Verification:
- 100 composed quizzes (sizes 1/5/10/25/53 x 20 seeds) x 3 versions =
  300 total renders, all producing well-formed HTML (valid DOCTYPE
  through closing tag, balanced <div> pairs, no leaked undefined/NaN
  text).
- Confirmed exactly 1 '(correct)' marker per question in teacher-
  version output (not more, not fewer) across a 15-question quiz
  including 6 figure-bearing questions, with each question's exact
  figureSvg string confirmed present in the rendered HTML.
- Confirmed the answer-key page appears only in 'both' version and
  never leaks '(correct)' markers into the student-facing question
  list of that same version.
- Rejection path confirmed for a null/invalid quiz object.

This completes the full path from certified template to
classroom-ready document: Registry -> ... -> Distractor Engine ->
Prompt Renderer -> Question Factory -> Quiz Composer -> Quiz Printer.
